      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions documented; turbulence model selection justified for rotating machinery hemolysis application.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on literature review of rotating blood-contacting device simulations. Model form assumptions documented in simulation plan. Sensitivity to turbulence model assessed via supplemental k-epsilon comparison; RH predictions differ by less than 6%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties, geometric inputs, and boundary conditions traceable to measurement or published reference data.",
      "rationale": "Blood analog viscosity measured with calibrated rheometer (Brookfield DV3T). Pump geometry digitized from manufacturer CAD with dimensional verification. Inlet velocity profiles derived from upstream flow conditioner characterization. All inputs traceable and documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
